text: Meanus () is a small village in County Limerick, Ireland, about 19km South of Limerick City. The village has a Catholic church, a GAA Pitch (Camogue Rovers GAA), 2 pubs (Dempseys Bar and The Hogan Stand), and a community centre. The River Camogue runs close to the village. Nearby villages include Fedamore, Bruff, Athlacca, Croom, and Crecora. Category:Towns and villages in County Limerick
title: Meanus
